Simplified Geo Parser for Census Crosswalks

Source: R/parse_geo_main.R
parse_geo.Rd

This function takes in simplified user inputs, filters either the tract or block datasets based on these inputs and returns the relevant FIPS codes

Usage

parse_geo(
  census.level,
  geo.region = NULL,
  geo.state = NULL,
  geo.county = NULL,
  geo.city = NULL
)

Arguments

census.level

character scalar. Name of crosswalk, either 'tract' or 'block'.

geo.region

character vector. Name of geographic region. Acceptable values are 'South', 'West', 'Northeast' and 'Midwest'. Default == NULL.

geo.state

character vector. 2 letter state abbreviations. Values such as 'NY', 'CA', 'WY' are accepted. Default == NULL.

geo.county

character vector. Name of county. Case insensitive. Default == NULL.

geo.city

character vector. Name of city. State should be entered in geo.state. Case insensitive. Default == NULL.

Value

a character vector of either census tract or block FIPS.

Details

All arguments are nested. Hence only the FIPs that are present in all filters are returned.
